HEADWORD: Camelopard
<hw>Ca*mel"o*pard</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧*m⟦ecr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*p⟦aum⟧rd <it>or</it>
k⟦acr⟧m"⟦ecr⟧l*⟦osl⟧*p⟦aum⟧rd; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>camelopardus</ets>, L. <ets>camelopardalus</ets>,
<ets>camelopardalis</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>kamhlopa`rdalis</grk>;
<grk>ka`mhlos</grk> a camel + <grk>pa`rdalis</grk> pard, leopard: cf. F.
<ets>cam⟦eacute⟧lopard</ets>. The camelopard has a neck and head like a
